.TH "drm_mode_create_tile_group" 9 "drm_mode_create_tile_group" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_create_tile_group \- create a tile group from a displayid description
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_tile_group *" drm_mode_create_tile_group
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char topology[8] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "topology" 12
8-bytes unique per monitor.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a tile group for the unique monitor, and get a unique
identifier for the tile group.
.SH "RETURN"
new tile group or NULL.
